You can make this bootable by using OSCDIMG. I made this bootable by using the following command, replacing of course the paths with ones fitting my own computer:

oscdimg -n -m -bc:\efi-dvd\boot\etfsboot.com c:\efi-dvd c:\efi-iso\server2008dvd.iso

The article about it can be found here:
http://blog.aproductofsociety.org/?p=13

I got it to boot inside Virtual PC 2007, but as that piece of software doesn't support 64-bit emulation, I only the message that it had encountered a problem loading. But it did load instead of giving me a "Code 5" or some other BS.

Great, didn't see that this was the 32-bit I was commenting on :) What I described should still work, so good luck. The resulting image can be burned with IMGBURN or other burning software of your choosing.
